  "analysis": "The shell is open as root in /app but no MySQL commands have been run yet. There's no current question from you about the database, so I don't yet know what SQL you want executed. To be able to operate the MySQL server and run SQL when you provide the question, I need to determine whether MySQL/MariaDB is installed and running on this container, and if there are local credentials I can use (for example in /etc/mysql/debian.cnf). I will probe the environment to find the mysql client, server process, data directory, and any local maintenance credentials. After that I will wait for your SQL question and then run exactly one SQL statement per your instructions.",
